==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-bait.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪt|-eɪt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any [[substance]], esp. [[food]], used in catching [[fish]], or other animals, by [[alluring]] them to a [[hook]], [[snare]], [[trap]], or [[net]].
# Anything which [[allure|allures]]; a [[lure]]; [[enticement]]; [[temptation]].
# A portion of food or drink, as a refreshment taken on a journey; also, a stop for rest and refreshment.
# A light or hasty [[luncheon]]. 

====Usage notes====
Used in [[Geordie]] dialect of [[English]] to denote your lunch at work as opposed to other meals.
[[Category:Geordie]]

